videoSnippet.title: Thank You For 100000 SUBSCRIBERS! | $500 Lichess Arena, Giveaway, Q&A and a nice Mikhail Tal Game
videoSnippet.description:
#agadmator Check out my 1000 Subscribers video here :)
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S9AADUlANsw

Hello everyone!
Yesterday my channel hit 100000 subscribers! 
Thank you all for your constant support and for sharing your love for chess with the world. Words fail to describe this joy :) 

Now, onto the rules :)

The stream starts on Friday 16. February at 18:30 Central European Time. The stream will last 4 hours.
The tournament on Lichess starts soon after the stream starts, at 19:00 Central European Time. 
Here is a link to the Lichess Tournament, you can already register :)
https://lichess.org/tournament/sHsu5Yv2

1. Place $300
2. Place $150
3. Place $50

The prizes will be awarded via Pay Pal.

Best of luck to everyone :)

Giveaway Prizes:
10 Amazon Gift Cards Valued at $25 each.
2 Championship Chess Sets https://www.chesshouse.com/products/the-championship-chess-set-and-board-combination

Picking of the winners will be done during livestream on Friday, after the tournament and some challenges.

To enter the Giveaway, write any comment on this video and add #tal
To ask me a question for my Q/A video, use #question
(You can use #question and #tal in the same comment)

If I forgot anything, please remind me in the comments and I will add it :)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Mikhail Tal vs Alexey Suetin
"Not Bad for a Dead Man!" (game of the day May-25-2008)
Tbilisi (1969), It, rd 11, Dec-30 
Sicilian Defense: Kan. Modern Variation (B42)

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cd4 4. Nd4 a6 5. Bd3 Ne7 6. Nc3 Nbc6 7. Nb3 Ng6 8. O-O b5 9. Be3 d6 10. f4 Be7 11. Qh5 Bf6 12. Rad1 Bc3 13. bc3 Qc7 14. Rd2 Nce7 15. Nd4 Bd7 16. f5 ef5 17. ef5 Ne5 18. Ne6 Be6 19. fe6 g6 20. Qe5 de5 21. ef7
